{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-page-js","path":"/midas-heritage/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2>Introduction, history, best practice, structure &#x26; dictionary</h2>\n<p>In 1998, not long after ICOM produced an international data standard for archaeological sites and monument recording (1995), FISH produced a UK version called <em>MIDAS</em>. In 2007 it was expanded to include related information such as GIS (spatial data) and maritime components.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://historicengland.org.uk/images-books/publications/midas-heritage/\">MIDAS Heritage</a> is a British cultural heritage standard for recording information on buildings, monuments, archaeological sites, shipwrecks and submerged landscapes, parks and gardens, battlefields, artefacts and ecofacts.</p>\n<p>The data standard suggests the minimum level of information needed for recording heritage assets and covers the procedures involved in understanding, protecting and managing these assets. It is used by national government organizations, local authorities, heritage sector organizations, amenity groups and societies, the research community and professional contractors.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 35.58282208588957%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/747e1bc0ae28a3c503aa764912fe9425/98307/MIDAS_Heritage_logo.webp 163w,\n/static/747e1bc0ae28a3c503aa764912fe9425/92d89/MIDAS_Heritage_logo.webp 325w,\n/static/747e1bc0ae28a3c503aa764912fe9425/8ea29/MIDAS_Heritage_logo.webp 650w,\n/static/747e1bc0ae28a3c503aa764912fe9425/55e68/MIDAS_Heritage_logo.webp 975w,\n/static/747e1bc0ae28a3c503aa764912fe9425/cadae/MIDAS_Heritage_logo.webp 1300w,\n/static/747e1bc0ae28a3c503aa764912fe9425/91d33/MIDAS_Heritage_logo.webp 1831w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/747e1bc0ae28a3c503aa764912fe9425/9d4d6/MIDAS_Heritage_logo.png 163w,\n/static/747e1bc0ae28a3c503aa764912fe9425/59727/MIDAS_Heritage_logo.png 325w,\n/static/747e1bc0ae28a3c503aa764912fe9425/c8518/MIDAS_Heritage_logo.png 650w,\n/static/747e1bc0ae28a3c503aa764912fe9425/bcba3/MIDAS_Heritage_logo.png 975w,\n/static/747e1bc0ae28a3c503aa764912fe9425/9a3b8/MIDAS_Heritage_logo.png 1300w,\n/static/747e1bc0ae28a3c503aa764912fe9425/f52e1/MIDAS_Heritage_logo.png 1831w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/747e1bc0ae28a3c503aa764912fe9425/c8518/MIDAS_Heritage_logo.png\"\n            alt=\"MIDAS Heritage logo\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">MIDAS Heritage logo</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<div class=\"text-center\"><a href=\"/2015/10/MIDAS_Heritage_2012_update_v5.doc\" class=\"btn btn-success text-center\">Download the standard</a></div>\n<h3>History</h3>\n<p>The first edition, <em>MIDAS â€“ A Manual and Data Standard for Monument Inventories</em>, was published by the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_Commission_on_the_Historical_Monuments_of_England\">Royal Commission on the Historical Monuments of England</a> (RCHME) in 1998. The second edition, published in 2007, was published by <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/English_Heritage\">English Heritage</a> (today <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Historic_England\">Historic England</a>).</p>\n<p>The standard was developed for and on behalf of the <em>Forum on Information Standards in Heritage</em> (FISH), a discussion forum aimed at helping to resolve standards and recording issues for the whole of the heritage sector.</p>\n<h3>Best Practice</h3>\n<p>MIDAS Heritage incorporates elements from several different standards, such as:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.collectionstrust.org.uk/collections-link/collections-management/spectrum/the-spectrum-standard\">SPECTRUM</a> (artefacts)</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.agi.org.uk/agi-groups/standards-committee/uk-gemini\">UK Gemini Discovery Metadata Standard</a> (GIS / geographic information)</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.cidoc-crm.org/\">CIDOC Conceptual Reference Model</a> (concepts and relationships)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://khub.net/web/uk-her-manual\">UK HER Manual</a> (how to manage a dynamic HER)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>MIDAS Heritage complies with the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E-GMS\">UK e-Government Metadata Standard</a> (e-GMS), which is based on <a href=\"http://dublincore.org/documents/dces/\">Dublin Core</a>.</p>\n<p>The standard aims only to provide a common information framework and does not cover:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>what software or file format to use</li>\n<li>what to call fields and tables in a database and how they are designed</li>\n<li>what indexing terms to use</li>\n<li>how to record archives and museum collections</li>\n<li>how to redesign an existing information system</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Structure</h3>\n<p>MIDAS Heritage groups historic environment information into six main <em>themes</em> (e.g. Spatial Information), which consist of more specific <em>information groups</em> (e.g. Location), which all contain a number of specific <em>information units</em> (e.g. Postcode).</p>\n<ol>\n<li><em>Heritage Assets:</em> Areas, Monuments, Artefacts and ecofacts  (<em>Watercraft and Aircraft</em>)</li>\n<li><em>Activities:</em> Investigative activities, Designation and protection, Heritage asset management activities, Casework and consultations, Research and analysis, Historical events</li>\n<li><em>Information Sources:</em> Archive and bibliography, Narrative and synthesis, Management activity documentation</li>\n<li><em>Spatial Information:</em> Location, Map depiction</li>\n<li><em>Temporal Information:</em> Dates and periods</li>\n<li><em>Actor Information:</em> Actor and role information</li>\n</ol>\n<p>NB! The <em>Watercraft and Aircraft Annexe</em> is available as a separate document.</p>\n<div class=\"text-center\"><a href=\"/2015/10/MIDAS_Watercraft_and_Aircraft_complete-1.pdf\" class=\"btn btn-success text-center\">Download the Watercraft and Aircraft Annexe</a></div>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 201px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 149.07975460122697%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/43a1a9c25e275d45372ef2ce0d1533ea/98307/midas-heritage-image-consultation-201x300.webp 163w,\n/static/43a1a9c25e275d45372ef2ce0d1533ea/1ff6e/midas-heritage-image-consultation-201x300.webp 201w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 201px) 100vw, 201px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/43a1a9c25e275d45372ef2ce0d1533ea/9d4d6/midas-heritage-image-consultation-201x300.png 163w,\n/static/43a1a9c25e275d45372ef2ce0d1533ea/bb31a/midas-heritage-image-consultation-201x300.png 201w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 201px) 100vw, 201px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/43a1a9c25e275d45372ef2ce0d1533ea/bb31a/midas-heritage-image-consultation-201x300.png\"\n            alt=\"Casework and Consultation - Hanover Square, London Â© Historic England. Man and woman looking at drawings or diagrams, standing in front of a building, smiling.\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Casework and Consultation - Hanover Square, London Â© Historic England. Man and woman looking at drawings or diagrams, standing in front of a building, smiling.</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 199px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 150.920245398773%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/5f46ead24789c033822fcf5523c37ece/98307/excavation-midas-heritage-image-199x300.webp 163w,\n/static/5f46ead24789c033822fcf5523c37ece/48dc9/excavation-midas-heritage-image-199x300.webp 199w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/5f46ead24789c033822fcf5523c37ece/9d4d6/excavation-midas-heritage-image-199x300.png 163w,\n/static/5f46ead24789c033822fcf5523c37ece/5bedf/excavation-midas-heritage-image-199x300.png 199w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/5f46ead24789c033822fcf5523c37ece/5bedf/excavation-midas-heritage-image-199x300.png\"\n            alt=\"Investigative Activity - Ashby de la Zouch Castle, Leicestershire. Â© Historic England. Image of a man with an archaeological instrument, standing next to an excavated section in the foreground.\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Investigative Activity - Ashby de la Zouch Castle, Leicestershire. Â© Historic England. Image of a man with an archaeological instrument, standing next to an excavated section in the foreground.</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h3>Dictionary</h3>\n<p>The <a href=\"/2015/10/MIDAS-Heritage-Dictionary-March-2016-PDF.pdf\">MIDAS Heritage Dictionary</a> recommends what information units to include when recording a particular asset or management area, and explains how they should be used. A few information units are mandatory but the majority are optional, depending on the purpose of your inventory.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>There are some minor discrepancies with the Mandatory/ Optional status for a few individual information units which we are aware of and plan to address in the near future.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Each unit of information contains a brief description, guidance on usage, whether a field is free text or controlled and should be populated using a terminology list/ authority file, and one or more examples.</p>\n<div class=\"text-center\"><a href=\"/2015/10/MIDAS-Heritage-Dictionary-March-2016-PDF.pdf\" class=\"btn btn-success text-center\">Download the Dictionary</a></div>","id":"a8ad1e25-3732-5fc7-8d1c-a14ce23dec91","timeToRead":2,"wordCount":{"words":570},"frontmatter":{"permalink":"/midas-heritage/","date":"April 08, 2014","last_modified_at":"August 27, 2024","title":"Midas Heritage","author":["Digital Standards Unit"]}}},"pageContext":{"permalink":"/midas-heritage/","id":"a8ad1e25-3732-5fc7-8d1c-a14ce23dec91"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2494122958","3133867949","4037206124"],"slicesMap":{}}